<!--Build a modern, production-ready developer portfolio using HTML5, CSS3 and Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+). Follow these exact requirements and output complete files (index.html, style.css, script.js) with no external libraries:

Minimal HTML shell: only semantic containers and IDs for sections; all repeated content must be generated by JavaScript.
Data-driven rendering: store nav, hero, about, hobbies and games data in arrays/objects and generate DOM using explicit for loops (no forEach, map, templates, or server rendering).
Sections to implement:
Navigation: sticky, glassmorphism style, keyboard accessible, mobile menu toggle, active-link highlighting based on scroll (use IntersectionObserver). Include a navItems array to render links.
Hero: eyebrow, headline, subtitle, rotating typed words (typing + deleting animation cycling through an array), primary & secondary CTAs, small SVG illustration, and decorative highlights rendered from an array.
About: profile image (use imageSrc), paragraphs, technologies list, statistic cards. If imageSrc fails, show an inline SVG fallback via onerror. Render techs, paragraphs and stats from arrays with for loops.
Games/Hobbies: separate #games section rendered from a GAMES array; hobby chips in About rendered from a HOBBIES array.
JavaScript structure: provide modular functions renderNavigation(), renderHero(), renderAbout(), renderGames(), plus initMenu(), initActiveSection(), initReveal(), initTyping() and call them on DOMContentLoaded.
Accessibility & semantics: use proper landmarks, aria attributes for menu toggles, focus states, and ensure keyboard operability.
Styling: use CSS variables, backdrop-filter for glass effect, responsive layout with grid/flex. Keep styles in style.css.
Performance & graceful fallback: avoid blocking scripts, favor CSS transitions, ensure images have fallbacks, keep only essential DOM and minimal inline SVGs.
No frameworks, no build tools required. All code must be plain HTML/CSS/JS and work by opening index.html in a browser.
Mention where to put the profile image: assets/images/profile.jpg (recommended ~800×800). Do not require the image to exist—fallback must be inline SVG.